         <p outputclass="box" class="- topic/p ">SAS No. 142 explains what constitutes audit evidence in an
                        audit of financial statements and sets out attributes of information that
                        are taken into account by the auditor when evaluating information to be used
                        as audit evidence.</p>
         <p outputclass="box" class="- topic/p ">This SAS is effective for audits of financial statements for
                        periods ending on or after December 15, 2022. A link to the final SAS and
                        other resources can be found on the page “<xref scope="external" format="html" class="- topic/xref " href="https://www.aicpa.org/interestareas/frc/auditattest/auditing-standards-information-and-resources.html">Recently Issued Auditing and Attestation Standards: Information and
                            Resources</xref>,” which is available using the audit and attest link in
                        the financial reporting center at aicpa.org.</p>
      </note>
